reviews.review_text: David the Bass Player I met David at Syracuse University my 2nd semester and he turned me on to recording live music. He had a huge collection of tapes... & Played Bass in a couple of local bands. I also met a guy Randy who ran a few record stores in the area who was a collector as well & his collection was even bigger. We traded a ton of shows and he would give us blanks.. it was a good trade as they say on the Rez. This was the first Dead show I recorded myself with my behemoth Marantz Superscope 330D that was the size of a dictionary and weighed as much & ate D cells for snacks...LoL I still wonder how I was able to sneak that thing in to so many shows.
